  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Cash Management Specialist (Banking)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job ID: 1399163</strong><br /><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Acquire and onboard <strong>New-to-Bank (NTB) SME clients</strong>, building a sustainable and profitable portfolio</p></li><li><p>Actively manage and grow an assigned SME portfolio through deep client engagement and needs-based solutions</p></li><li><p>Achieve and exceed <strong>quarterly sales targets</strong> aligned to a clear and transparent scorecard</p></li><li><p>Drive business development through <strong>lead generation, networking, referrals, and market outreach</strong></p></li><li><p>Provide end-to-end SME banking solutions, including:</p><ul><li><p>Business accounts and cash management</p></li><li><p>Working capital and lending solutions</p></li><li><p>Trade finance and FX</p></li><li><p>Investments, insurance, and hedging solutions</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Structure and recommend appropriate financial solutions based on clients’ business models, cash flow cycles, and risk profiles</p></li><li><p>Price products prudently while balancing commercial value and risk considerations</p></li><li><p>Maintain strong, long-term client relationships with consistently high service standards</p></li><li><p>Ensure full compliance with <strong>KYC, Customer Due Diligence</strong>, and internal/regulatory policies</p></li></ul><p><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul><li><p>Bachelor’s degree or equivalent</p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>2 years of experience</strong> in SME banking, cash management, and/or lending</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of <strong>SME products, working capital cycles, and cash flow management</strong></p></li><li><p>Familiarity with <strong>CDD requirements</strong>, including FATCA and CRS</p></li><li><p>Proven ability in <strong>sales, portfolio growth, and cross-selling</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong communication, negotiation, and stakeholder management skills</p></li><li><p>High standards of professionalism, integrity, and regulatory discipline</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Why This Role</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Clear focus on <strong>New-to-Bank acquisition</strong>, ideal for RMs who enjoy hunting and deal-making</p></li><li><p>Exposure to a <strong>full SME banking suite</strong>, not a single-product role</p></li><li><p>Strong platform, brand credibility, and internal support</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to build a long-term career within <strong>SME / Commercial Banking</strong></p></li></ul><p><em>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. However, all applications will be retained in our resume bank for future opportunities.</em><br />Privacy Policy: <a href=\"https://goodjobcreations.com.sg/en/privacy-policy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">https://goodjobcreations.com.sg/en/privacy-policy/</a></p><p><strong>EA Personnel Name:</strong> Tan Gabriel<br /><strong>EA Personnel Reg. No.:</strong> R22104076<br /><strong>EA License No.:</strong> 07C5771<br /><strong></strong></p>",
